{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ed988829-c186-4cf7-8fda-2a36bf7006f0","agentId":"aa28e0abdc3b5ed74","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Do focused WEB research (WebSearch + WebFetch; cite URLs) to inform a design decision for a local self-evolving agent (\"Yogi\") on a 16 GB Apple Silicon Mac (M5 MacBook Pro). Do not answer from memory alone.\n\nDECISION: feasibility + best approach for an on-device per-domain DISTILLATION FLYWHEEL within 16 GB unified memory. The intended loop: a teacher (`qwen3:8b` served by Ollama) generates quality-filtered traces on a domain; those traces train a SMALL student via LoRA; the student then handles that domain more cheaply. Everything foreground, one model loaded at a time.\n\nResearch and answer concretely:\n1. **Student size feasible to LoRA/QLoRA fine-tune within 16 GB unified memory.** Is qwen3:8b trainable at 16 GB (likely no)? What about qwen3 1.7B / 0.6B / 4B, or Llama-3.2-1B/3B? Give real memory figures for LoRA/QLoRA fine-tuning at these sizes on Apple Silicon.\n2. **Best framework on Apple Silicon for LoRA fine-tuning** and serving the result: MLX / MLX-LM vs candle vs llama.cpp finetune vs PyTorch-MPS vs unsloth. Which actually works well on M-series within 16 GB, and can the trained adapter then be served locally (via Ollama, an MLX server, or merged to GGUF)?\n3. **Teacher→student workflow within 16 GB** (sequential: run teacher to collect traces, unload, then train student — never both resident). Rough training time + peak memory for one small per-domain LoRA.\n4. **The honest verdict:** is real weight-space distillation practical at 16 GB for a research build, or should it be a rare, foreground, small-student operation while the everyday compounding comes from elsewhere?\n\nEND WITH a concrete RECOMMENDATION for Yogi M3: pick a student model + method + framework + workflow that fits 16 GB foreground, OR recommend deferring/minimizing weight distillation. Cite URLs throughout. Return findings only; do not edit files."},"uuid":"4e69663e-beff-4324-b8d2-08f33880f047","timestamp":"2026-06-21T03:49:48.504Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
