{"parentUuid":"9a70618f-7c07-4223-a922-562f7c51e61a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa28e0abdc3b5ed74","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01VCv8DZp8o1SupLjtCLXfNd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QQxQkssnvB1yfWLi2CRzLq","name":"WebSearch","input":{"query":"QLoRA fine-tuning memory requirements 1B 3B 7B model VRAM"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1003,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7188,"cache_read_input_tokens":5357,"output_tokens":174,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7188},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1003,"output_tokens":174,"cache_read_input_tokens":5357,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7188,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7188,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"tools_changed","cache_missed_input_tokens":8406}}},"requestId":"req_011CcFiuR4qZ4MCsnaHicJ4L","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","type":"assistant","uuid":"16cc6071-0c21-4ab9-b5df-8f2d63bfcc2d","timestamp":"2026-06-21T03:49:55.384Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"9a70618f-7c07-4223-a922-562f7c51e61a","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ed988829-c186-4cf7-8fda-2a36bf7006f0","agentId":"aa28e0abdc3b5ed74","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012gZURue6sWwyycp5M6vxi3","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"MLX LoRA fine-tuning memory usage Apple Silicon 16GB Llama 7B\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Fine-Tuning LLMs Locally Using MLX LM\",\"url\":\"https://dzone.com/articles/fine-tuning-llms-locally-using-mlx-lm-guide\"},{\"title\":\"Fine-Tuning on Mac: LoRA & QLoRA with MLX | InsiderLLM\",\"url\":\"https://insiderllm.com/guides/fine-tuning-mac-lora-mlx/\"},{\"title\":\"Fine-Tuning LLMs with LoRA and MLX-LM | by Joana Levtcheva | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@levchevajoana/fine-tuning-llms-with-lora-and-mlx-lm-c0b143642deb\"},{\"title\":\"Choosing an On-Device LLM Runtime on Apple Silicon: A Decision Framework Beyond Benchmarks\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@michael.hannecke/choosing-an-on-device-llm-runtime-on-apple-silicon-a-decision-framework-beyond-benchmarks-2449067b8b67\"},{\"title\":\"MLX Apple Silicon AI Dev Stack: Fine-Tune LLMs on Mac\",\"url\":\"https://www.buildmvpfast.com/blog/mlx-apple-silicon-ai-development-mac-fine-tune-llm-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Local AI Therapy: Fine-Tuning Mistral-7B on Apple Silicon with MLX & LoRA (M3 Max Performance!) 🚀 - DEV Community\",\"url\":\"https://dev.to/wellallytech/local-ai-therapy-fine-tuning-mistral-7b-on-apple-silicon-with-mlx-lora-m3-max-performance-2kj3\"},{\"title\":\"Fine-Tuning Guide: Customize Your LLM with LoRA\",\"url\":\"https://www.e-accelerate.com/finetuning.html\"},{\"title\":\"Train Your Own LLM on MacBook: A Fine-tuning Guide with MLX | by Dushyant Mahajan | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@dummahajan/train-your-own-llm-on-macbook-a-15-minute-guide-with-mlx-6c6ed9ad036a\"},{\"title\":\"Fine-Tuning Open-Source LLMs with Apple's MLX ...\",\"url\":\"https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/fine-tuning-open-source-llms-apples-mlx-framework-guide-vishnu-n-c-ylqrc\"},{\"title\":\"LoRA Fine-Tuning On Your Apple Silicon MacBook | Towards Data Science\",\"url\":\"https://towardsdatascience.com/lora-fine-tuning-on-your-apple-silicon-macbook-432c7dab614a/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about MLX LoRA fine-tuning memory usage for Llama 7B on Apple Silicon with 16GB:\n\n## Memory Requirements\n\nFor Llama-7B models, memory usage breaks down as follows: Full Precision requires ~28 GB, LoRA (r=8) requires ~14 GB, and QLoRA (4-bit + LoRA) requires ~7 GB.\n\n## Feasibility on 16GB Apple Silicon\n\nThe good news is that fine-tuning is feasible on 16GB unified memory systems, but with some considerations:\n\nQLoRA quantization enables fine-tuning 7B parameter models on consumer hardware with as little as 16GB of unified memory. However, standard LoRA at ~14GB leaves limited headroom on a 16GB system.\n\nApple's unified memory architecture means your entire RAM pool is available for training with no separate VRAM limit, and a MacBook Pro with unified memory can use all available memory (minus what macOS needs) for training.\n\n## Practical Performance\n\nFor real-world training metrics: Training Mistral-7B on 5,000 examples takes roughly 90 minutes on an M2 Max with 32GB, with peak memory around 7GB (using QLoRA).\n\n## Recommendations if Memory is Tight\n\nIf you're hitting memory limits, you can quantize the base model, reduce batch size, reduce the number of fine-tuned layers, break examples into shorter sequences, or enable gradient checkpointing.\n\n**Bottom line**: While standard LoRA at 14GB is tight on 16GB systems, QLoRA with 4-bit quantization at ~7GB memory usage is the recommended approach for comfortable headroom.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"bb082a71-fe34-4a33-90c2-bfe5b8582af4","timestamp":"2026-06-21T03:50:03.791Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"MLX LoRA fine-tuning memory usage Apple Silicon 16GB Llama 7B","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_0133nP55X9wKMd6UBfWqfDub","content":[{"title":"Fine-Tuning LLMs Locally Using MLX LM","url":"https://dzone.com/articles/fine-tuning-llms-locally-using-mlx-lm-guide"},{"title":"Fine-Tuning on Mac: LoRA & QLoRA with MLX | InsiderLLM","url":"https://insiderllm.com/guides/fine-tuning-mac-lora-mlx/"},{"title":"Fine-Tuning LLMs with LoRA and MLX-LM | by Joana Levtcheva | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/@levchevajoana/fine-tuning-llms-with-lora-and-mlx-lm-c0b143642deb"},{"title":"Choosing an On-Device LLM Runtime on Apple Silicon: A Decision Framework Beyond Benchmarks","url":"https://medium.com/@michael.hannecke/choosing-an-on-device-llm-runtime-on-apple-silicon-a-decision-framework-beyond-benchmarks-2449067b8b67"},{"title":"MLX Apple Silicon AI Dev Stack: Fine-Tune LLMs on Mac","url":"https://www.buildmvpfast.com/blog/mlx-apple-silicon-ai-development-mac-fine-tune-llm-2026"},{"title":"Local AI Therapy: Fine-Tuning Mistral-7B on Apple Silicon with MLX & LoRA (M3 Max Performance!) 🚀 - DEV Community","url":"https://dev.to/wellallytech/local-ai-therapy-fine-tuning-mistral-7b-on-apple-silicon-with-mlx-lora-m3-max-performance-2kj3"},{"title":"Fine-Tuning Guide: Customize Your LLM with LoRA","url":"https://www.e-accelerate.com/finetuning.html"},{"title":"Train Your Own LLM on MacBook: A Fine-tuning Guide with MLX | by Dushyant Mahajan | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/@dummahajan/train-your-own-llm-on-macbook-a-15-minute-guide-with-mlx-6c6ed9ad036a"},{"title":"Fine-Tuning Open-Source LLMs with Apple's MLX ...","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/fine-tuning-open-source-llms-apples-mlx-framework-guide-vishnu-n-c-ylqrc"},{"title":"LoRA Fine-Tuning On Your Apple Silicon MacBook | Towards Data Science","url":"https://towardsdatascience.com/lora-fine-tuning-on-your-apple-silicon-macbook-432c7dab614a/"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found about MLX LoRA fine-tuning memory usage for Llama 7B on Apple Silicon with 16GB:\n\n## Memory Requirements\n\nFor Llama-7B models, memory usage breaks down as follows: Full Precision requires ~28 GB, LoRA (r=8) requires ~14 GB, and QLoRA (4-bit + LoRA) requires ~7 GB.\n\n## Feasibility on 16GB Apple Silicon\n\nThe good news is that fine-tuning is feasible on 16GB unified memory systems, but with some considerations:\n\nQLoRA quantization enables fine-tuning 7B parameter models on consumer hardware with as little as 16GB of unified memory. However, standard LoRA at ~14GB leaves limited headroom on a 16GB system.\n\nApple's unified memory architecture means your entire RAM pool is available for training with no separate VRAM limit, and a MacBook Pro with unified memory can use all available memory (minus what macOS needs) for training.\n\n## Practical Performance\n\nFor real-world training metrics: Training Mistral-7B on 5,000 examples takes roughly 90 minutes on an M2 Max with 32GB, with peak memory around 7GB (using QLoRA).\n\n## Recommendations if Memory is Tight\n\nIf you're hitting memory limits, you can quantize the base model, reduce batch size, reduce the number of fine-tuned layers, break examples into shorter sequences, or enable gradient checkpointing.\n\n**Bottom line**: While standard LoRA at 14GB is tight on 16GB systems, QLoRA with 4-bit quantization at ~7GB memory usage is the recommended approach for comfortable headroom."],"durationSeconds":8.378817291999992,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"9a70618f-7c07-4223-a922-562f7c51e61a","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"16cc6071-0c21-4ab9-b5df-8f2d63bfcc2d","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ed988829-c186-4cf7-8fda-2a36bf7006f0","agentId":"aa28e0abdc3b5ed74","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QQxQkssnvB1yfWLi2CRzLq","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"QLoRA fine-tuning memory requirements 1B 3B 7B model VRAM\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"How can I fine-tune large language models on a budget using LoRA and QLoRA on cloud GPUs?\",\"url\":\"https://www.runpod.io/articles/guides/how-to-fine-tune-large-language-models-on-a-budget\"},{\"title\":\"Fine tuning GPU memory requirements · ggml-org/llama.cpp · Discussion #2904\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp/discussions/2904\"},{\"title\":\"How much VRAM do I need for LLM model fine-tuning?\",\"url\":\"https://modal.com/blog/how-much-vram-need-fine-tuning\"},{\"title\":\"LLM Fine-Tuning Hardware Requirements: VRAM, GPU\",\"url\":\"https://llmhardware.io/guides/llm-fine-tuning-hardware-requirements\"},{\"title\":\"Fine-tuning LLaMA-7B on ~12GB VRAM with QLoRA, 4-bit quantization · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://gist.github.com/Birch-san/57878c4a27cf34f57d3e861865a7d0a2\"},{\"title\":\"Fine-Tuning Infrastructure: LoRA, QLoRA, and PEFT at Scale | Introl Blog\",\"url\":\"https://introl.com/blog/fine-tuning-infrastructure-lora-qlora-peft-scale-guide-2025\"},{\"title\":\"How Much VRAM Do You Need for LLM Fine-Tuning in 2026? - VRLA Tech\",\"url\":\"https://vrlatech.com/how-much-vram-do-you-need-for-llm-fine-tuning-in-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Fine-Tune LLMs with LoRA and QLoRA: 2026 Guide - DEV Community\",\"url\":\"https://dev.to/jangwook_kim_e31e7291ad98/fine-tune-llms-with-lora-and-qlora-2026-guide-33lf\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here are the QLoRA fine-tuning memory requirements for different model sizes:\n\n## Memory Requirements Summary\n\n**For QLoRA fine-tuning:**\n\n- A 7B model in 4-bit requires ~3.5 GB base model plus ~8-10 GB overhead, and can run comfortably on a 16 GB GPU. More specifically, a 7B model needs ~12 GB VRAM with QLoRA.\n\n- A 13B in 4-bit requires ~6.5 GB base model plus overhead, with 13B QLoRA fitting on a 24 GB GPU.\n\n**For 1B and 3B models:**\n\nWhile the search results don't provide explicit numbers for 1B models, you can extrapolate: LoRA generally requires about 2 GB of GPU memory per 1B parameters for the model weights plus some overhead for LoRA and optimizer. QLoRA would use roughly 4x less memory than standard LoRA for the base model weights.\n\n**Key advantages of QLoRA:**\n\nFor QLoRA (4-bit base model), you cut the base model numbers by 4× compared to standard LoRA. QLoRA typically achieves 80–90% of full fine-tuning performance, compared to 90–95% for standard LoRA.\n\nThese memory requirements are significantly lower than full fine-tuning, which would require 60-120 GB VRAM for comparable model sizes.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"115e0d0c-9091-491b-9312-fb93521f4363","timestamp":"2026-06-21T03:50:04.381Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"QLoRA fine-tuning memory requirements 1B 3B 7B model VRAM","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01JD1AbPTYUgEojpZg2RzVMJ","content":[{"title":"How can I fine-tune large language models on a budget using LoRA and QLoRA on cloud GPUs?","url":"https://www.runpod.io/articles/guides/how-to-fine-tune-large-language-models-on-a-budget"},{"title":"Fine tuning GPU memory requirements · ggml-org/llama.cpp · Discussion #2904","url":"https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp/discussions/2904"},{"title":"How much VRAM do I need for LLM model fine-tuning?","url":"https://modal.com/blog/how-much-vram-need-fine-tuning"},{"title":"LLM Fine-Tuning Hardware Requirements: VRAM, GPU","url":"https://llmhardware.io/guides/llm-fine-tuning-hardware-requirements"},{"title":"Fine-tuning LLaMA-7B on ~12GB VRAM with QLoRA, 4-bit quantization · GitHub","url":"https://gist.github.com/Birch-san/57878c4a27cf34f57d3e861865a7d0a2"},{"title":"Fine-Tuning Infrastructure: LoRA, QLoRA, and PEFT at Scale | Introl Blog","url":"https://introl.com/blog/fine-tuning-infrastructure-lora-qlora-peft-scale-guide-2025"},{"title":"How Much VRAM Do You Need for LLM Fine-Tuning in 2026? - VRLA Tech","url":"https://vrlatech.com/how-much-vram-do-you-need-for-llm-fine-tuning-in-2026/"},{"title":"Fine-Tune LLMs with LoRA and QLoRA: 2026 Guide - DEV Community","url":"https://dev.to/jangwook_kim_e31e7291ad98/fine-tune-llms-with-lora-and-qlora-2026-guide-33lf"}]},"Based on the search results, here are the QLoRA fine-tuning memory requirements for different model sizes:\n\n## Memory Requirements Summary\n\n**For QLoRA fine-tuning:**\n\n- A 7B model in 4-bit requires ~3.5 GB base model plus ~8-10 GB overhead, and can run comfortably on a 16 GB GPU. More specifically, a 7B model needs ~12 GB VRAM with QLoRA.\n\n- A 13B in 4-bit requires ~6.5 GB base model plus overhead, with 13B QLoRA fitting on a 24 GB GPU.\n\n**For 1B and 3B models:**\n\nWhile the search results don't provide explicit numbers for 1B models, you can extrapolate: LoRA generally requires about 2 GB of GPU memory per 1B parameters for the model weights plus some overhead for LoRA and optimizer. QLoRA would use roughly 4x less memory than standard LoRA for the base model weights.\n\n**Key advantages of QLoRA:**\n\nFor QLoRA (4-bit base model), you cut the base model numbers by 4× compared to standard LoRA. QLoRA typically achieves 80–90% of full fine-tuning performance, compared to 90–95% for standard LoRA.\n\nThese memory requirements are significantly lower than full fine-tuning, which would require 60-120 GB VRAM for comparable model sizes."],"durationSeconds":8.610242499999993,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"16cc6071-0c21-4ab9-b5df-8f2d63bfcc2d","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
