{"parentUuid":"eb621c98-35ee-4070-8273-860989535f5e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ed988829-c186-4cf7-8fda-2a36bf7006f0","agentId":"aa28e0abdc3b5ed74","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BPeTSvDeQyqnVMtKsUpM1L","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Qwen3 0.6B 1.7B 4B LoRA fine-tuning MLX Apple Silicon memory\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Qwen 3.5 on Apple Silicon MLX (2026) — Memory Usage, Tokens/sec & Setup Guide | Will It Run AI Blog\",\"url\":\"https://willitrunai.com/blog/qwen-3-5-mlx-apple-silicon-guide\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - sciences44/mlx-lora-finetune: Fine-tune Qwen3.5 for Text-to-SQL on your Mac with MLX LoRA — no GPU required. 4-model comparison, prompt engineering benchmark, and honest limitations.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/sciences44/mlx-lora-finetune\"},{\"title\":\"Fine-Tuning on Mac: LoRA & QLoRA with MLX | InsiderLLM\",\"url\":\"https://insiderllm.com/guides/fine-tuning-mac-lora-mlx/\"},{\"title\":\"Fine-Tuning LLMs with LoRA and MLX-LM | by Joana Levtcheva | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@levchevajoana/fine-tuning-llms-with-lora-and-mlx-lm-c0b143642deb\"},{\"title\":\"LoRA Fine-Tuning On Your Apple Silicon MacBook | Towards Data Science\",\"url\":\"https://towardsdatascience.com/lora-fine-tuning-on-your-apple-silicon-macbook-432c7dab614a/\"},{\"title\":\"MLX Apple Silicon AI Dev Stack: Fine-Tune LLMs on Mac\",\"url\":\"https://www.buildmvpfast.com/blog/mlx-apple-silicon-ai-development-mac-fine-tune-llm-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Fine-Tuning LLMs Locally Using MLX LM\",\"url\":\"https://dzone.com/articles/fine-tuning-llms-locally-using-mlx-lm-guide\"},{\"title\":\"Best LLM for Mac 2026: Picks for M1/M2/M3/M4 by RAM Tier | Will It Run AI Blog\",\"url\":\"https://willitrunai.com/blog/best-llm-for-mac-apple-silicon-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Train Your Own LLM on MacBook: A Fine-tuning Guide with MLX | by Dushyant Mahajan | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@dummahajan/train-your-own-llm-on-macbook-a-15-minute-guide-with-mlx-6c6ed9ad036a\"},{\"title\":\"Choosing an On-Device LLM Runtime on Apple Silicon: A Decision Framework Beyond Benchmarks\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@michael.hannecke/choosing-an-on-device-llm-runtime-on-apple-silicon-a-decision-framework-beyond-benchmarks-2449067b8b67\"}]\n\nI found comprehensive information about Qwen models and LoRA fine-tuning with MLX on Apple Silicon. Here are the key findings:\n\n## LoRA Fine-Tuning Support\n\nMLX natively supports LoRA and QLoRA fine-tuning on Apple Silicon. This makes it possible to fine-tune Qwen models on Apple Silicon Macs efficiently.\n\n## Memory Requirements by Model Size\n\nThe search results focus primarily on larger Qwen3.5 models, but here are the relevant memory guidelines:\n\n- A 14B model needs ~14-18GB for LoRA training, which is tight on a 24GB GPU but comfortable on a 32GB Mac.\n- A 32B model at QLoRA needs ~20-25GB.\n\nFor smaller models like the 0.6B, 1.7B, and 4B variants you mentioned, memory requirements would be substantially lower.\n\n## Practical Fine-Tuning Example\n\nTraining Mistral-7B on 5,000 examples takes roughly 90 minutes on an M2 Max with 32GB, and peak memory sits around 7GB. This demonstrates that MLX fine-tuning is quite memory-efficient compared to traditional approaches.\n\n## Apple Silicon Unified Memory Advantage\n\nApple Silicon's unified memory means your 16/36/64/96 GB of RAM is your VRAM. No data transfers between CPU and GPU. No OOM surprises. The model lives in one place, and the GPU reads it directly.\n\nThe search results don't contain specific benchmark data for the exact model sizes you mentioned (0.6B, 1.7B, 4B), but the general principles show that smaller models would require significantly less memory than the 14B+ examples provided.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"e0e5503a-078a-4db7-a50f-1a14785e919d","timestamp":"2026-06-21T03:50:33.920Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Qwen3 0.6B 1.7B 4B LoRA fine-tuning MLX Apple Silicon memory","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01MkuPQShHwaJ6Zntf3bSKXS","content":[{"title":"Qwen 3.5 on Apple Silicon MLX (2026) — Memory Usage, Tokens/sec & Setup Guide | Will It Run AI Blog","url":"https://willitrunai.com/blog/qwen-3-5-mlx-apple-silicon-guide"},{"title":"GitHub - sciences44/mlx-lora-finetune: Fine-tune Qwen3.5 for Text-to-SQL on your Mac with MLX LoRA — no GPU required. 4-model comparison, prompt engineering benchmark, and honest limitations.","url":"https://github.com/sciences44/mlx-lora-finetune"},{"title":"Fine-Tuning on Mac: LoRA & QLoRA with MLX | InsiderLLM","url":"https://insiderllm.com/guides/fine-tuning-mac-lora-mlx/"},{"title":"Fine-Tuning LLMs with LoRA and MLX-LM | by Joana Levtcheva | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/@levchevajoana/fine-tuning-llms-with-lora-and-mlx-lm-c0b143642deb"},{"title":"LoRA Fine-Tuning On Your Apple Silicon MacBook | Towards Data Science","url":"https://towardsdatascience.com/lora-fine-tuning-on-your-apple-silicon-macbook-432c7dab614a/"},{"title":"MLX Apple Silicon AI Dev Stack: Fine-Tune LLMs on Mac","url":"https://www.buildmvpfast.com/blog/mlx-apple-silicon-ai-development-mac-fine-tune-llm-2026"},{"title":"Fine-Tuning LLMs Locally Using MLX LM","url":"https://dzone.com/articles/fine-tuning-llms-locally-using-mlx-lm-guide"},{"title":"Best LLM for Mac 2026: Picks for M1/M2/M3/M4 by RAM Tier | Will It Run AI Blog","url":"https://willitrunai.com/blog/best-llm-for-mac-apple-silicon-2026"},{"title":"Train Your Own LLM on MacBook: A Fine-tuning Guide with MLX | by Dushyant Mahajan | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/@dummahajan/train-your-own-llm-on-macbook-a-15-minute-guide-with-mlx-6c6ed9ad036a"},{"title":"Choosing an On-Device LLM Runtime on Apple Silicon: A Decision Framework Beyond Benchmarks","url":"https://medium.com/@michael.hannecke/choosing-an-on-device-llm-runtime-on-apple-silicon-a-decision-framework-beyond-benchmarks-2449067b8