{"parentUuid":"018f65e3-45c7-43f9-93f4-a8031a39e758","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ed988829-c186-4cf7-8fda-2a36bf7006f0","agentId":"aa28e0abdc3b5ed74","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01L74iLhR7KoFwNqME2xnMZe","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"knowledge distillation teacher generated synthetic data small student model LoRA does it work quality\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Agentic Knowledge Distillation: Autonomous Training of Small Language Models for SMS Threat Detection\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2602.10869\"},{\"title\":\"Knowledge Distillation: Bridging the Gap Between Qwen3-Next-80B-A3B-Instruct and Mistral-7B-v0.1 | by Frank Morales Aguilera | AI Simplified in Plain English | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/ai-simplified-in-plain-english/knowledge-distillation-bridging-the-gap-between-qwen3-next-80b-a3b-instruct-and-mistral-7b-v0-1-7cc1f0c5d8c7\"},{\"title\":\"TiTok: Transfer Token-level Knowledge via Contrastive Excess to Transplant LoRA\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2510.04682v1\"},{\"title\":\"LoRA-Enhanced Vision Transformer for Single Image based Morphing Attack Detection via Knowledge Distillation from EfficientNet\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2511.12602v1\"},{\"title\":\"Advancing Model Refinement: Muon-Optimized Distillation and Quantization for LLM Deployment\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.09865\"},{\"title\":\"Privacy-Preserving Reasoning with Knowledge-Distilled Parametric Retrieval Augmented Generation\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2509.01088\"},{\"title\":\"Weight Copy and Low-Rank Adaptation for Few-Shot Distillation of Vision   Transformers\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2404.09326\"},{\"title\":\"Synthetic data generation method for data-free knowledge distillation in   regression neural networks\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2301.04338\"},{\"title\":\"Communication-Aware Knowledge Distillation for Federated LLM Fine-Tuning over Wireless Networks\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2509.01750\"},{\"title\":\"Aligning Sizes of Intermediate Layers by LoRA Adapter for ...\",\"url\":\"https://aclanthology.org/2025.insights-1.10.pdf\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what research shows about knowledge distillation with teacher-generated synthetic data for small student models using LoRA:\n\n## Does It Work?\n\nYes—the best configurations achieve 94.31% accuracy and 96.25% recall in practical applications. Agentic knowledge distillation substantially outperforms direct preference optimization baselines that use the same synthetic knowledge and LoRA setup.\n\n## Quality and Effectiveness\n\nGenerating a dataset directly from the teacher model eliminates the need for curated datasets, reducing costs and enabling customization. However, quality depends on the teacher: teacher LLM capability significantly impacts student SLM performance, with substantial variation in final accuracy and precision-recall balance across teacher LLMs.\n\n## How It Works in Practice\n\nThe teacher LLM autonomously generates synthetic data and iteratively refines a smaller on-device student model until performance plateaus. By leveraging 4-bit quantization and LoRA, the approach enables distillation on hardware with 24–40GB VRAM, democratizing access to advanced NLP techniques.\n\n## Additional Research\n\nSynthetic data generation enhances knowledge distillation by creating diverse teacher-annotated datasets, though some approaches require quality filtering mechanisms. The combination of teacher-generated synthetic data with LoRA fine-tuning appears to be an effective and increasingly practical approach for deploying smaller models.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"c663f96a-7256-4645-92a7-1d8cc66e5788","timestamp":"2026-06-21T03:50:47.551Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"knowledge distillation teacher generated synthetic data small student mo