ations achieve 94.31% accuracy and 96.25% recall in practical applications. Agentic knowledge distillation substantially outperforms direct preference optimization baselines that use the same synthetic knowledge and LoRA setup.\n\n## Quality and Effectiveness\n\nGenerating a dataset directly from the teacher model eliminates the need for curated datasets, reducing costs and enabling customization. However, quality depends on the teacher: teacher LLM capability significantly impacts student SLM performance, with substantial variation in final accuracy and precision-recall balance across teacher LLMs.\n\n## How It Works in Practice\n\nThe teacher LLM autonomously generates synthetic data and iteratively refines a smaller on-device student model until performance plateaus. By leveraging 4-bit quantization and LoRA, the approach enables distillation on hardware with 24–40GB VRAM, democratizing access to advanced NLP techniques.\n\n## Additional Research\n\nSynthetic data generation enhances knowledge distillation by creating diverse teacher-annotated datasets, though some approaches require quality filtering mechanisms. The combination of teacher-generated synthetic data with LoRA fine-tuning appears to be an effective and increasingly practical approach for deploying smaller models."],"durationSeconds":7.346968332999997,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"018f65e3-45c7-43f9-93f4-a8031a39e758","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
