{"parentUuid":"512fc52b-8bb6-4e93-826f-5647f5805fcb","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa28e0abdc3b5ed74","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_013ZxLtJN4RbQYiQMHMkmhZB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015Uk9FoyJ4mUdrW7re7XMiV","name":"WebFetch","input":{"url":"https://github.com/ml-explore/mlx/discussions/1507","prompt":"What is the recommended way to convert an MLX-trained LoRA adapter (adapters.safetensors) to GGUF for Ollama, especially for Qwen models that aren't Llama/Mistral architecture? Does fuse to safetensors then llama.cpp convert_hf_to_gguf.py work for Qwen3? Any pitfalls?"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1360,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1364,"cache_read_input_tokens":21521,"output_tokens":392,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1364},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1360,"output_tokens":392,"cache_read_input_tokens":21521,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1364,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1364,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcFiyvJMS1KUFxxKqP9QX","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","type":"assistant","uuid":"ab740bc8-88be-443b-9e92-beeab48ca545","timestamp":"2026-06-21T03:50:58.689Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"512fc52b-8bb6-4e93-826f-5647f5805fcb","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ed988829-c186-4cf7-8fda-2a36bf7006f0","agentId":"aa28e0abdc3b5ed74","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NxvWRZuprLcNeSLEuVWK4V","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"unsloth Apple Silicon MPS support macOS fine-tuning 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"GitHub - ARahim3/mlx-tune: Fine-tune LLMs on your Mac with Apple Silicon. SFT, DPO, GRPO, Vision, TTS, STT, Embedding, and OCR fine-tuning — natively on MLX. Unsloth-compatible API.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/ARahim3/mlx-tune\"},{\"title\":\"Unsloth Requirements | Unsloth Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://unsloth.ai/docs/get-started/fine-tuning-for-beginners/unsloth-requirements\"},{\"title\":\"Introducing Unsloth-MLX Fine-tune LLMs on your Mac with ...\",\"url\":\"https://www.facebook.com/0xSojalSec/posts/introducing-unsloth-mlx-fine-tune-llms-on-your-mac-with-apple-silicon-same-api-a/1412391123748620/\"},{\"title\":\"Unsloth-MLX download | SourceForge.net\",\"url\":\"https://sourceforge.net/projects/unsloth-mlx.mirror/\"},{\"title\":\"Fine-Tuning on a MacBook: MLX, 3 Minutes, 90 Examples, and a Model That Actually Works | by florinelchis | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://florinelchis.medium.com/fine-tuning-on-a-macbook-mlx-3-minutes-90-examples-and-a-model-that-actually-works-7de0547da347\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - masna-ai/unsloth-mlx: Bringing the Unsloth experience to Mac users via Apple's MLX framework · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/masna-ai/unsloth-mlx\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Unsloth and Apple Silicon MPS support for macOS fine-tuning:\n\n## Official Unsloth Status\n\nApple/Silicon/MLX support is in the works according to the official Unsloth documentation. However, Unsloth currently has no Mac support planned and is CUDA-only.\n\n## Alternative Solutions\n\nSince native Unsloth doesn't support Apple Silicon, the community has developed alternatives:\n\n1. **MLX-based approaches**: Unsloth-MLX (and similar projects like mlx-tune) offer developers the Unsloth experience on Apple Silicon Macs by wrapping Apple's native MLX framework with an API fully compatible with Unsloth workflows.\n\n2. **Why the workaround exists**: Unsloth relies on Triton (which Macs don't have, yet), making direct Mac support infeasible.\n\n3. **MLX framework**: MLX (mlx-lm) offers first-class Apple Silicon support for fine-tuning tasks like QLoRA.\n\nThe unofficial projects like mlx-tune and unsloth-mlx allow you to use Unsloth-compatible APIs on your Mac by leveraging Apple's MLX framework, enabling code portability between local Mac prototyping and cloud GPU training.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"b7c796c8-423a-4832-9fa0-43ea2574f17c","timestamp":"2026-06-21T03:51:02.968Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"unsloth Apple Silicon MPS support macOS fine-tuning 2026","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01923qD1QVcXpQAwyphcXdLd","content":[{"title":"GitHub - ARahim3/mlx-tune: Fine-tune LLMs on your Mac with Apple Silicon. SFT, DPO, GRPO, Vision, TTS, STT, Embedding, and OCR fine-tuning — natively on MLX. Unsloth-compatible API.","url":"https://github.com/ARahim3/mlx-tune"},{"title":"Unsloth Requirements | Unsloth Documentation","url":"https://unsloth.ai/docs/get-started/fine-tuning-for-beginners/unsloth-requirements"},{"title":"Introducing Unsloth-MLX Fine-tune LLMs on your Mac with ...","url":"https://www.facebook.com/0xSojalSec/posts/introducing-unsloth-mlx-fine-tune-llms-on-your-mac-with-apple-silicon-same-api-a/1412391123748620/"},{"title":"Unsloth-MLX download | SourceForge.net","url":"https://sourceforge.net/projects/unsloth-mlx.mirror/"},{"title":"Fine-Tuning on a MacBook: MLX, 3 Minutes, 90 Examples, and a Model That Actually Works | by florinelchis | Medium","url":"https://florinelchis.medium.com/fine-tuning-on-a-macbook-mlx-3-minutes-90-examples-and-a-model-that-actually-works-7de0547da347"},{"title":"GitHub - masna-ai/unsloth-mlx: Bringing the Unsloth experience to Mac users via Apple's MLX framework · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/masna-ai/unsloth-mlx"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found about Unsloth and Apple Silicon MPS support for macOS fine-tuning:\n\n## Official Unsloth Status\n\nApple/Silicon/MLX support is in the works according to the official Unsloth documentation. However, Unsloth currently has no Mac support planned and is CUDA-only.\n\n## Alternative Solutions\n\nSince native Unsloth doesn't support Apple Silicon, the community has developed alternatives:\n\n1. **MLX-based approaches**: Unsloth-MLX (and similar projects like mlx-tune) offer developers the Unsloth experience on Apple Silicon Macs by wrapping Apple's native MLX framework with an API fully compatible with Unsloth workflows.\n\n2. **Why the workaround exists**: Unsloth relies on Triton (which Macs don't have, yet), making direct Mac support infeasible.\n\n3. **MLX framework**: MLX (mlx-lm) offers first-class Apple Silicon support for fine-tuning tasks like QLoRA.\n\nThe unofficial projects like mlx-tune and unsloth-mlx allow you to use Unsloth-compatible APIs on your Mac by leveraging Apple's MLX framework, enabling code portability between local Mac prototyping and cloud GPU training."],"durationSeconds":5.9034500419999825,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"512fc52b-8bb6-4e93-826f-5647f5805fcb","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"ab740bc8-88be-443b-9e92-beeab48ca545","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ed988829-c186-4cf7-8fda-2a36bf7006f0","agentId":"aa28e0abdc3b5ed74","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015Uk9FoyJ4mUdrW7re7XMiV","type":"tool_result","content":"# Converting MLX LoRA Adapters to GGUF\n\nBased on the GitHub discussion, here's what we know:\n\n## The Conversion Process\n\nThe recommended approach involves:\n\n1. **Converting adapters.safetensors to HF PEFT format** using a transformation script that:\n   - Renames keys following the pattern: `model.layers.0.self_attn.q_proj.lora_a` → `base_model.model.model.layers.0.self_attn.q_proj.lora_A.weight`\n   - Transposes tensors appropriately\n   - Converts `adapter_config.json` to PEFT-compatible format\n\n2. **Using llama.cpp's conversion tool**: \"python convert_lora_to_gguf.py --base <path to your base model> --outtype q8_0 <path to the converted adapter>\"\n\n## Important Limitation\n\nThe discussion focuses on Gemma and doesn't address Qwen-specific considerations. The original question mentions keeping adapters separate rather than fusing, but there's no Qwen3-specific guidance provided.\n\n## What the Content Doesn't Cover\n\n- Whether this approach works for non-Llama architectures like Qwen\n- Qwen3-specific compatibility issues\n- Validation that the fuse-to-safetensors→llama.cpp conversion path is optimal\n\n**Recommendation**: Test with a small Qwen3 model first, and consider opening an issue in the mlx or llama.cpp repositories if architecture-specific problems arise."}]},"uuid":"24800ace-db8a-43ea-9037-5a891ffc81d8","timestamp":"2026-06-21T03:51:06.687Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":406541,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Converting MLX LoRA Adapters to GGUF\n\nBased on the GitHub discussion, here's what we know:\n\n## The Conversion Process\n\nThe recommended approach involves:\n\n1. **Converting adapters.safetensors to HF PEFT format** using a transformation script that:\n   - Renames keys following the pattern: `model.layers.0.self_attn.q_proj.lora_a` → `base_model.model.model.layers.0.self_attn.q_proj.lora_A.weight`\n   - Transposes tensors appropriately\n   - Converts `adapter_config.json` to PEFT-compatible format\n\n2. **Using llama.cpp's conversion tool**: \"python convert_lora_to_gguf.py --base <path to your base model> --outtype q8_0 <path to the converted adapter>\"\n\n## Important Limitation\n\nThe discussion focuses on Gemma and doesn't address Qwen-specific considerations. The original question mentions keeping adapters separate rather than fusing, but there's no Qwen3-specific guidance provided.\n\n## What the Content Doesn't Cover\n\n- Whether this approach works for non-Llama architectures like Qwen\n- Qwen3-specific compatibility issues\n- Validation that the fuse-to-safetensors→llama.cpp conversion path is optimal\n\n**Recommendation**: Test with a small Qwen3 model first, and consider opening an issue in the mlx or llama.cpp repositories if architecture-specific problems arise.","durationMs":7778,"url":"https://github.com/ml-explore/mlx/discussions/1507"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ab740bc8-88be-443b-9e92-beeab48ca545","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
